TITLE: Putin speaks out about Wagner Group rebellion
SUMMARY: Russian President Putin addressed his nation for the first time since the Wagner Group’s rebellion, saying it was a “militarized mutiny” committed by “traitors.” The whereabouts of the group’s chief Yevgeny Prigozhin, who released his own message earlier on Monday, is still unknown

TITLE: Mutiny and mayhem in Russia a probable boon for Ukraine
SUMMARY: The armed revolt may be an opportunity for Kyiv's forces, but Vladimir Putin's woes and vulnerability could also make the Russian leader more dangerous, analysts said

TITLE: Myanmar torches drugs worth half a billion dollars as illicit trade soars
